      <![CDATA[<p>Some of my friends are really good at this demonic game. Since I’m not a very skilled gamer, it’s impossible for me to win fairly. But maybe I can win <em>unfairly</em>. Let’s try sending our own better score.</p><h2 id="How-is-the-score-sent"><a href="#How-is-the-score-sent" class="headerlink" title="How is the score sent?"></a>How is the score sent?</h2><p>Time to fire up Burp Suite and start inspecting the HTTPS requests. I had to play at least once, but I ended up playing eight times to gather more data. In the image below, you can see one of the POST requests. This request is triggered when you complete the level of the day. It’s an API call named <code>submit-score</code>, so it’s a no-brainer that this will be a crucial part of the hacking process.</p><img src="/2026/02/19/kinda_easy_hack/image_1.png" class=""><p>There’s a lot of information in the request, but the most important part is the data at the end. We have pretty straightforward names: score, infuriatingMode, isFirstAttempt; and one strange field: q.</p><p>Let’s try sending this request to the repeater and changing the score to 1. We do it, send it, and—done—the response is <em>“Score submitted!”</em>. I check the scoreboard, and of course, it’s not that easy. The server performs a check and discards our score without telling us. This might slow us down because we now have to verify manually, but it also tells us that <code>q</code> is probably something we should focus on.</p><h2 id="What-is-q"><a href="#What-is-q" class="headerlink" title="What is q?"></a>What is q?</h2><p><code>q</code> is likely some kind of hash based on the other fields. But how can we confirm this? Let’s achieve the same score multiple times. The JSON below represents the data sent each time I finished the game. Notice that the last two times, the score and <code>q</code> are identical:</p><figure class="highlight json"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="punctuation">&#123;</span><span class="attr">&quot;score&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="number">45</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;clientDate&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;2026-02-18&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;q&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;0b731fe0&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;infuriatingMode&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;isFirstAttempt&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">true</span></span><span class="punctuation">&#125;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="punctuation">&#123;</span><span class="attr">&quot;score&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="number">38</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;clientDate&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;2026-02-18&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;q&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;3405097c&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;infuriatingMode&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;isFirstAttempt&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">&#125;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="punctuation">&#123;</span><span class="attr">&quot;score&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="number">29</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;clientDate&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;2026-02-18&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;q&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;4d33a85a&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;infuriatingMode&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;isFirstAttempt&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">&#125;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="punctuation">&#123;</span><span class="attr">&quot;score&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="number">35</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;clientDate&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;2026-02-18&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;q&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;1cf0195f&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;infuriatingMode&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;isFirstAttempt&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">&#125;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="punctuation">&#123;</span><span class="attr">&quot;score&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="number">42</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;clientDate&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;2026-02-18&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;q&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;0ba1d03d&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;infuriatingMode&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;isFirstAttempt&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">&#125;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="punctuation">&#123;</span><span class="attr">&quot;score&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="number">36</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;clientDate&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;2026-02-18&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;q&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;24a1bebe&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;infuriatingMode&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;isFirstAttempt&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">&#125;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="punctuation">&#123;</span><span class="attr">&quot;score&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="number">40</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;clientDate&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;2026-02-18&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;q&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;1b051afb&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;infuriatingMode&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;isFirstAttempt&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">&#125;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="punctuation">&#123;</span><span class="attr">&quot;score&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="number">40</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;clientDate&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;2026-02-18&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;q&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="string">&quot;1b051afb&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;infuriatingMode&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">,</span><span class="attr">&quot;isFirstAttempt&quot;</span><span class="punctuation">:</span><span class="literal"><span class="keyword">false</span></span><span class="punctuation">&#125;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Now it’s time to figure out how to generate a <code>q</code> for any given score.</p><h2 id="How-is-q-computed"><a href="#How-is-q-computed" class="headerlink" title="How is q computed?"></a>How is q computed?</h2><p>Javascript games are usually executed in client-side, so we should have the source code. It’s probably some type of obfuscated ugly 1 million lines of code file so we just use Inspect Element and search the keyword: “submit-score”. Just 1 occurrence, let’s download and check that spaghetti code. </p><p>Since I am more C than javascript inclined I don’t really want to read that, so I resort to some “Vibe reversing” (new slang of my creation) like it’s said in Lucas 15:21 “Father, I have sinned against heaven and against you. I am no longer worthy to be called your son.”. And yes, all of that is true.</p><img src="/2026/02/19/kinda_easy_hack/image_2.png" class=""><p>After all the controversy I get the de-obfuscated  function that creates q:</p><figure class="highlight javascript"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">function</span> <span class="title function_">makeQ</span>(<span class="params">score, date</span>)&#123;</span><br><span class="line">  <span class="keyword">const</span> s = <span class="string">`<span class="subst">$&#123;score&#125;</span>:<span class="subst">$&#123;date&#125;</span>`</span>;</span><br><span class="line">  <span class="keyword">let</span> h = <span class="number">0</span>;</span><br><span class="line">  <span class="keyword">for</span> (<span class="keyword">let</span> i=<span class="number">0</span>;i&lt;s.<span class="property">length</span>;i++)&#123;</span><br><span class="line">    h = (h&lt;&lt;<span class="number">5</span>) - h + s.<span class="title function_">charCodeAt</span>(i);</span><br><span class="line">    h |= <span class="number">0</span>;</span><br><span class="line">  &#125;</span><br><span class="line">  <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="title class_">Math</span>.<span class="title function_">abs</span>(h).<span class="title function_">toString</span>(<span class="number">16</span>).<span class="title function_">padStart</span>(<span class="number">8</span>,<span class="string">&quot;0&quot;</span>);</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>So it basically has its own hash function and uses the concatenation of score and date for the generation of q. I translated from javascript to python:</p><figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title function_">make_q</span>(<span class="params">score, date</span>):</span><br><span class="line">    s = <span class="string">f&quot;<span class="subst">&#123;score&#125;</span>:<span class="subst">&#123;date&#125;</span>&quot;</span></span><br><span class="line">    h = <span class="number">0</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">for</span> ch <span class="keyword">in</span> s:</span><br><span class="line">        h = (h &lt;&lt; <span class="number">5</span>) - h + <span class="built_in">ord</span>(ch)  <span class="comment"># h * 31 + char</span></span><br><span class="line">        h &amp;= <span class="number">0xFFFFFFFF</span>  </span><br><span class="line">    </span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">if</span> h &amp; <span class="number">0x80000000</span>:</span><br><span class="line">        h = -((~h + <span class="number">1</span>) &amp; <span class="number">0xFFFFFFFF</span>)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="built_in">format</span>(<span class="built_in">abs</span>(h), <span class="string">&quot;08x&quot;</span>)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># example</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">if</span> __name__ == <span class="string">&quot;__main__&quot;</span>:</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="built_in">print</span>(make_q(<span class="number">40</span>, <span class="string">&quot;2026-02-18&quot;</span>))</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>We tried with 40 and the result is correct: 1b051afb.</p><h2 id="Results"><a href="#Results" class="headerlink" title="Results"></a>Results</h2><p>Now it’s time to check if the score has been added to the leaderboard—and yes, it has! If you’re skeptical about the truth of this claim, you can always verify it in the official game Discord. It seems some anonymous punk is so good at this game that they reached the finish flag in just <strong>five throws</strong>. The community is astonished:</p><img src="/2026/02/19/kinda_easy_hack/image_3.png" class=""><p>I love the different approaches about the physical impossibility of the score. Some theories about impossible throws:</p><img src="/2026/02/19/kinda_easy_hack/image_4.png" class=""><p>Happy hacking lads!</p>]]>
